title: No. 7 Michigan State at No. 12 Michigan, plus more Top 25 college football scores
text:
The Michigan Wolverines are a surprising 5-1 in the first year of the Jim Harbaugh era.
Since a Week 1 loss to now-No. 4 Utah in Salt Lake City, the Maize and Blue have outscored opponents 160-14 – including three consecutive shutouts – winning their last four games in a row heading into Saturday's intrastate rivalry with Michigan State (6-0). Now the Wolverines hope that momentum will carry over against the No. 7 Spartans, who have won six of the last seven meetings in the series.
